message: the markings show the Afghan Ministry of Defense logo that was commonly seen on Tanks in the late 1980s and early 1990s

After 1990 the ruling party of Afghanistan was renamed the Homeland Party which featured many PDPA Members but also members of the former Daoud Khan government of the 70s. Also Democratic was removed from the name of Afghanistan in 1987.

The AIG was not the state of Afghanistan. It was a Umbrella organization created in 1988 which hoped to be recognized as the legitimate government of Afghanistan (Although their were plans to recognize it following the Battle of Jalalabad due to the failure to take Jalalabad the AIG was never recognized.) The AIG would eventually become the Islamic State of Afghanistan in 1992.
